writer_one:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "It is time to take your article to The Pulp Writer and receive her judgement."
        "[Show your article to The Pulp Writer] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 1):
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inMap false
            add_stat actions -1
            set_button button_writer_one false
            run transition_black writer_door
            clear_dialog
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump game_map
            
    choice:
        "A haggered apartment tucked away in a small alley on the edge of Bluehills. A cobbled walkway that, if it were not littered with refuse, would be quite beautiful. You climb rusting metal stairs outside the building to the second floor of the brick structure. This is where The Pulp Writer resides."
        "[Knock on the door]":
            play sound doorknock
            "There is the sound of awkward, clumsy movement inside."
            clear_dialog
            talk lovely talk "Let us try to make a good impression on her, yes? This morning was rather embarrassing for us, truth be told."
    clear_dialog
    play sound dooropen
    play music writer
    run transition_instant writer_door_open
    "The door opens a crack. A grey eye lit by an orange ember glares out at you for a moment before the door is opened fully."
    clear_dialog
    if $data.global.writerNaked:
        talk writer talk "Ah. It's you, and you've remembered to get dressed this time, I see."
        clear_dialog
        "The Pulp Writer, on the other hand is wearing the same sweater as she was this morning."
        if (roll writer_one_coat_orb orb 20):
            talk orb talk "She's practically inseparable from it. Rabies did some nasty work to her body temperature. She sleeps under enough blankets that it feels akin to the weight of another person atop her, though that's not *solely* motivated by lack of warmth."
        else:
            wait 1000
    else:
        talk writer talk "Ah. It's you."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "Without actually inviting you in she turns and heads inside."
        "[Follow The Pulp Writer to her apartment]":
            play sound doorclose
            jump writer_one_inside

writer_one_inside:
    clear_dialog
    run transition writer_apartment_both
    "The Pulp Writer's apartment is cluttered. It's perhaps comfortable for about eighty percent of the average mammal, or a single occupant, provided they don't much care for 'moving around'."
    "The Pulp Writer does not."
    clear_dialog
    "It smells of the smoke that forms a haze throughout the abode. It's the haze of a dream on an autumn morning."
    "It's littered with books. Notebooks, fiction, non-fiction. A thick tome titled <span class='writtenText'>'Apprendre l'espagnol'</span>..."
    if (roll writer_one_iberia_orb orb 40):
        talk orb talk "She's plotting a migration to the Iberian Republic. It's more tolerant of her politics, and she thinks the weather will do her good."
        talk orb talk "It's a pipe dream. She knows she will die, surrounded by the thorns of capital, here in Anglia."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "The Pulp Writer is about to speak, when they break into a coughing fit. It's a hacking, chest cough."
    "The kind of cough you hear from someone who's choking on viscera. They manage to cover their mouth with a tissue, sparing you the worst of their fit, but it lasts an uncomfortably long time. You feel her pain."
    "Then, when it is over, her eyes look into yours. It could be shame in them, or an apology, or resentment that you saw her like this. It's hard to tell."
    if (roll writer_one_cough_lovely lovely 60):
        talk lovely talk "It's all three."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "Then, as though they were never pointed anywhere else, her eyes snap back to her cigarette."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Asseyez-vo-, euh, have a seat."
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "More well mammered mannals would have begun that sentence with an <span class='writtenText'>'Excuse me'</span>, but if our friend here verbally apologised every time they broke out into a coughing fit they'd never get anything done."
    choice:
        talk orb talk "It's hardly a surprise. The Pulp Writer barely survived their time with second stage rabies."
        "You can *survive* second stage rabies?":
            "The writer looks into their tissue, at whatever it is that came out of their throat."
            if (roll writer_one_cough_orb orb 20):
                talk orb talk "Black, crusted blood. A hair thin slither of flesh. The word 'survive' can be comfortingly vague, sometimes."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Can I get you a drink?"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk lovely talk "Wine! Wheee! Squeak squeak!"
        "\\"A drink sounds nice!\\"":
            talk writer talk "Mhm. One moment."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "The Pulp Writer disappears into another room for a moment, before returning with some water."
                "\\"This is water.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Yes. Filtered and boiled. Alcohol is quite bad for you."
                    if (roll writer_one_packs_orb orb 40):
                        talk orb talk "She smokes *at least* two packs a day."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    talk lovely talk "Water!? How is one supposed to stay hydrated with this? Fetch the wine, serving girl!"
                    talk nasty talk "Did you seriously fucking just look at me when you said that?"
                "\\"Mmm yummy water. I love how plain it is.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "It cleanses the soul, a good glass of clean water. Nothing compares. Except smoking, one supposes."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "You know, we've kind of been forgetting to eat and drink since the accident. You should probably drink that water, Ghost."
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer sets your glass down on the table, next to the ashtray. Or the book. It's somewhat difficult to tell which it is."
            "Regardless of its status as ashtray, book or in-between, its title is 'Sous la couronne noire ou : Ciel d'épines', but the name of the author is illegible from years of poor treatment."
        "\\"No thank you.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Mhm. Well I'll be having one."
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer disappears into another room for a moment, before returning with some water."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "You know, we've kind of been forgetting to eat and drink since the accident. You should probably drink some water eventually, Ghost."
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer sets their glass down on the table, next to the ashtray. Or the book. It's somewhat difficult to tell which it is. Regardless of its status as ashtray, book or in-between, its title is 'Sous la couronne noire ou : Ciel d'épines', but the name of the author is illegible from years of poor treatment."
    clear_dialog
    talk orb talk "That is a serious fire hazard. Tsk."
    clear_dialog
    "The Pulp Writer seems to notice you gawping at the book, and sighs."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "My handywork. Ignore it. Certainly I try to."
        "\\"You wrote it?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Mhm. Unfortunately."
        "\\"Ignore it?\\"":
            talk writer talk "It's shit. I resent it's continued blight upon the world of literature and would rather forget it exists."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "Keeping on the table seems somewhat counterintuitive to that."
            talk nasty talk "Keep your enemies close... and your enemies closer..."
            talk lovely talk "Very true, Nasty Girl."
        "\\"You *try* to?\\"":
            talk writer talk "I have a problem with intrusive thoughts, unfortunately. While I am loathe to admit it, <span class='writtenText'>'L'appel du vide'</span> sometimes compels me to consider drafting a sequel."
            clear_dialog
            "She visibly shudders, and not from the cold air."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk nasty talk "She really fucking hates this book, huh?"
        "\\"Can I read it?\\"":
            talk writer talk "No."
            clear_dialog
            "Her eyes are locked onto yours for perhaps the first time since you met her."
            if (roll writer_one_book_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "If you reached out to pick up the book she would have zero qualms leaping over the table and throttling you to death, so don't do that."
            else:
                wait 1000
        "\\"Understandable. I feel the same way about most of the things I've done over the last day or so.\\"":
            "The Pulp Writer chuckles hoarsely. Her throat is still dry and bloodied."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Yes. I understand."
        "[Nod and move on from this deceptively book shaped minefield]":
            "The Pulp Writer sniffs, her eyes strain. It is as though she is trying to will the book out of view so she can forget about it."
    clear_dialog
    "There is an awkward silence. It hangs in the air as thickly as The Pulp Writer's cigarette smoke."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "I apologise for my terseness this morning. I let my stress get the better of me, for which I apologise."
    clear_dialog
    "She doesn't actually look up at you while she says this."
    if (roll writer_one_genuine_lovely lovely 40):
        talk lovely talk "She is being genuine, though. She's just not all too comfortable expressing sincerity face to face."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Anyhow. Your article. May I?"
        "[Pass your article over to The Pulp Writer]":
            complete_objective writer writerOne
            remove_item article 1
            "The Pulp Writer reads your article as emotionlessly as she would read a menu at a restaurant specialising in Anglian cuisine."
    clear_dialog
    if (> $data.article.points 2):
        if $data.global.makeUpAGuy:
            choice:
                talk writer talk "...You made up a guy, didn't you?"
                "\\"Yes.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "I knew it. No problem though, I was just curious. "
                "[Tug your collar and gulp] \\"N-no.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "You're a shit liar, Ghost."
                    "They chuckle."
                    talk writer talk "Writer though? Eh, pas mal..."
                    if (roll writer_one_inside_mal_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Not bad.'</span> She genuinely enjoys your writing style. It's very different from her own. More bouncy, more babbley, she can see your train of thought, if not follow it."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "\\"I'd argue that the guy made up me.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "What?"
                    talk orb talk "Seconded."
            if $data.article.badName:
                talk writer talk "I'll be changing the name of your made-up guy though. That's one place your creativity seems to have failed you... we can't submit an article with *that* as our heroes name, can we?"
                clear_dialog
                if $data.article.nameNasty:
                    talk nasty talk "ETF!?"
                    clear_dialog
                    talk nasty talk "I mean uh, idiot. Fucking moron, Ghost. I told you not to write <span class='writtenText'>'Lovely Lady'</span>."
                    talk lovely talk "Don't gaslight her, you awful woman! Squeak Squeak!"
                if $data.article.nameLovely:
                    talk lovely talk "Gasp! How rude! One might have to kill oneself!"
                if $data.article.nameGhost:
                    choice:
                        "She thinks for a moment, pondering on a new name for your 'OC' (Origami Character)'."
                        "\\"Um. [Raise your hand] That's my name, mam.\\"":
                            talk writer talk "Yes. Your name is darling but..."
                            clear_dialog
                            "It sounds briefly like she might be about to finish her sentence, but she doesn't."
                            if (roll writer_one_inside_name_nightmare nightmare 20):
                                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>She's thinking what we're all thinking. what an ugly name for you. it doesn't suit you at all. try... dave, maybe?</span>"
                                clear_dialog
                play sound write
                "She pulls out a pencil and scribbles something on your article."
                if (roll writer_one_name_orb orb 60):
                    talk orb talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Cassilda'</span>"
                else:
                    wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Guy inventor or not, I'm not paid enough to enforce the frankly non-existent integrity of this rag any more than I have to. Good work, Ghost."
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Tell me, are you into creative writing?"
                "\\"Yes.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Admirable, but don't be. It will destroy you."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She stubs out her smoke and immediately lights a new one."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Still, you're good at it, so don't let me put you off."
                "\\"Not really, no.\\"":
                    "The Pulp Writer smirks."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "You're wiser than you look."
                "\\"Maybe, what's in it for me.\\" [Lean forward, awaiting The Pulp Writer's proposal]":
                    talk writer talk "I'm not trying to establish a trade deal with you, Ghost. Only I was curious."
        else:
            talk writer talk "A well researched piece. Good work, Ghost."
            if (roll writer_one_inside_comment_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "The fact that she isn't commenting further is a compliment, don't worry."
            else:
                wait 1000
    else:
        jump writer_one_badEnd
    clear_dialog
    "The Pulp Writer gets up and hurriedly files your article away into the pile of paper on her work desk."
    "She's smiling. It looks wrong on her, like her face isn't quite used to it. She scratches the back of her hand, but only for a brief moment. This is the least anxious she has been all week."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "I've been fretting all day about this, you know? After that automobile crash of a meeting this morning I was genuinely unsure you were up to this."
    if (roll writer_one_inside_draft_orb orb 40):
        talk orb talk "There's a scrawled page in her notebook, a draft for her version of your article, if you had let her down. The Pulp Writer is incapable of not getting stressed about this stuff. All worst cases must be accounted for in her mind."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "She rummages around in her drawer for an envelope. It's had a cigarette put out on it, and then quickly been extinguished in a moment of clarity. This envelope contains your commission."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Here."
    add_stat money 30
    play sound coins
    clear_dialog
    "She passes you the money. You'll be voting tory any day now."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Thank you, Ghost. You did good."
    clear_dialog
    "They tap some ash from their cigarette onto the burnt book."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "I'll sleep well tonight."
    if (roll writer_one_inside_sleep_orb orb 80):
        talk orb talk "She won't."
    else:
        wait 1000
    if (roll writer_one_inside_genuine_lovely lovely 60):
        talk lovely talk "She's really glad you came through."
        talk nasty talk "Speaking of cameing. We should get to know her."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    if (! $data.ghost.shaved true):
        if (roll writer_one_inside_shave_nightmare nightmare 80):
            choice:
                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>Hey. You're still not shaven, remember? Your little untrimmed muzzle hairs are so fucking obvious to her. You need to get out of here. Now. Go home and fix yourself up you fucking slob.</span>"
                "I don't care.":
                    jump writer_one_shave
                "The Pulp Writer has untrimmed muzzle hairs too. Who cares?":
                    jump writer_one_shave
        else:
            wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            run transition writer_sofa
            jump writer_one_menu
    else:
        run transition writer_sofa
        jump writer_one_menu

writer_one_shave:
    choice:
        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>you do. she does.</span>"
        "I don't.":
            talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>Whatever. Just stay here and keep looking like shit. Not my problem.</span>"
            run transition writer_sofa
            jump writer_one_menu

writer_one_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "So, Ghost. What brought you to Weird Tails? And please, be honest, this isn't a job interview. Certainly you need not lie to my face about how the idea of writing for a pulp magazine has always been your long term passion."
        "\\"I'm not sure, actually.\\"":
            "The Pulp Writer frowns internally."
            talk writer talk "D'accord. I can respect that, I suppose."
            if (roll writer_one_menu_respect_lovely lovely 60):
                talk lovely talk "No she can't."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump writer_one_conclusion
        "\\"Well, writing for a pulp magazine has always been my long term passion.\\"":
            jump writer_one_passion
        "\\"Money.\\"":
            jump writer_one_money
        "\\"What brings me to Weird Tails? It's simple really, chicks. Dicks. Babes. Girls love smelly, unwashed authors.\\"":
            talk lovely talk "They most certainly do *not*."
            talk nasty talk "They do. They really do. *SO* true Ghost."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Mhm. I suppose that's fair. I can't personally vouch for that though."
            if (roll writer_one_menu_sweat_nasty nasty 60):
                talk nasty talk "Yes she can. She is *so* into sweat."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump writer_one_conclusion
        roll writer_one_menu_reason_orb orb 60 "Orb, why did I get a job writing for Weird Tails?":
            success "":
                talk orb talk "You genuinely enjoy this shit. Also, you need money to live. *Mostly* because you need money to live, actually."
                set data.writer.one_menu_reason true
                jump writer_one_menu
            failure "":
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "No idea. Look to your heart for guidance I guess."
                    "I thought *you* were my heart now?":
                        talk orb talk "Aw crackers."
                    "[Look to your heart]":
                        "Your heart doesn't respond. It was mashed into a pulp, if you recall."
                jump writer_one_menu
        "\\"Writing pulp novels is my passion, but *also* I need money to live.\\"" if $data.writer.one_reason:
            talk writer talk "Mmm. Yes. Classic."
            jump writer_one_conclusion

writer_one_passion:
    "The Pulp Writer rolls her eyes and sighs."
    if (roll writer_one_menu_roll_lovely lovely 20):
        talk lovely talk "That was a light-hearted eye roll sigh combination, in case you were worried."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "But really? Why?"
        "\\"I'm serious. Writing pulp is fun.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Curious."
            clear_dialog
            "She's staring you in the eye now."
            if (roll writer_one_passion_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She doesn't like doing this, but your willingness to admit that you love writing trash has her intrigued. She's trying to extract an understanding of your soul from your eye like an oil rig fucking the earths crust."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Well. I shan't fault you for it. I suppose Weird Tails wouldn't enjoy its success if my tastes were the norm..."
            jump writer_one_conclusion
        "\\"Money, I guess.\\"":
            jump writer_one_money
        "\\"Writing pulp novels is genuinely my passion, but also I need money to live.\\"" if $data.writer.one_reason:
            talk writer talk "Mmm. Yes. Classic."
            jump writer_one_conclusion

writer_one_money:
    talk writer talk "Mhm."
    clear_dialog
    "They sip their water and ponder your words."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "An understandable, if somewhat spineless motivation."
    if (roll writer_one_money_lovely lovely 40):
        talk lovely talk "That came out a lot meaner than she intended. She's already apologised to you, albeit internally and silently."
    else:
        wait 1000
    jump writer_one_conclusion

writer_one_conclusion:
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "I used to write in the pursuit of a better world. That my words might bring conciousness to the workers. They of course did not."
    clear_dialog
    "She shrugs, pretending really hard that she does not care."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Art is dead. The claws of capital throttled the artistes to death. Now is the time of schlock."
    clear_dialog
    "She thinks for a moment, picking at the back of her hand. A breath rattles through her throat. The sound of blood being squeezed through a sieve."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "I was going to be an artiste, a revolutionary. Now I am neither, and all that is left for me is dying."
    if (roll writer_one_conclusion_eyes_lovely lovely 20):
        choice:
            talk lovely talk "The look in her eyes says a thousand words."
            "Which words? I need details, Lovely Lady.":
                talk lovely talk "Don't put me on the spot, darling, I'm not a dictionary."
                if (roll writer_one_conclusion_eyes_nasty nasty 20):
                    talk nasty talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Bitterness', 'Resentment', 'Loss'. 'Yearning'. 'Ennui'.</span>"
                    talk lovely talk "Tsk. Don't show me up, Nasty Girl."
                else:
                    wait 1000
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "She was an optimist, once. As far as a Frank can be, at any rate. But it's all gone now. It's all gone. The woman here is all that is left. To decay is to at least fester on."
    clear_dialog
    "A clock ticks somewhere in the apartment. The Pulp Writer taps their glass to the rhythm."
    if (roll writer_one_conclusion_clock_orb orb 60):
        talk orb talk "The clock is seven minutes fast. The Pulp Writer is well aware of this, but the mental maths required to work out the actual time is less effort for her than actually fixing it."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk nasty talk "You should ask her about herself. She/They chicks dig it when you're interested in their lives, and she clearly wants to talk to someone, or she'd never have invited you in."
        "Even this chick? She seems kind of snappy and closed off.":
            talk nasty talk "That's because she is. Think of yourself as a miner and her as a delicious, tasty vein of lead."
            talk lovely talk "Nasty Girl is right. It's fun to make friends!"
            talk nasty talk "Yeah. And even more fun to get laid."
        "Good idea. Let's converse.":
            talk nasty talk "Converse? I said talk to her not... whatever the fuck that is, dickhead."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Pulp Writer glances at the clock. Her frown frowns."
        "\\"Tell me about yourself. I don't know many people in Bluehills and I want to make friends. Will you be my friend?\\"":
            "They raise an eyebrow."
            talk lovely talk "Well. That was a very honest segue, I'll give you that."
        "\\"I best be off.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Oh. Well. Okay then. You aren't imposing, if that's what you're concerned about."
            if (roll writer_one_conclusion_imposing_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "It strains her to say this. Peeking ones head from behind their blank, emotionless walls takes a great deal of bravery, and a greater still deal of energy."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "The Pulp Writer examines the back of her hand. Picking at it mentally."
                "\\"Okay. I'll stay. Tell me about yourself. I don't know many people in Bluehills and I want to make friends. Will you be my friend?\\"":
                    "The Pulp Writer's frown flickers for a moment. If you squint your eyes *just* right, it almost looks like a smile."
                    talk lovely talk "She's genuinely glad for the company."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "If it's any consolation, I don't have any 'friends' here either."
    if (roll writer_one_conclusion_friends_lovely lovely 60):
        talk lovely talk "She didn't have many in Pawris either. Her skin is stone, and her fur blades. Few have the foolhardy audacity to crawl t'wards her."
        talk orb talk "That bodes well. Good luck Ghost."
    else:
        wait 1000
    if (roll writer_one_conclusion_friends_nasty nasty 60):
        talk nasty talk "She's loved people. Even fucked them, but none of them ever stayed with her for long."
        talk lovely talk "She's never stayed with *them*, for long. There's a difference, and it's one that hurts her."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Go on then. Ask me something. What do you want to know?"
    jump writer_one_menu_two

writer_one_menu_two:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "She's looking you in the eye now. Judging you. She wouldn't normally talk about herself, but around you she feels open. Perhaps it is how big and stupid your eyes are?"
        "\\"How old are you?\\"":
            "The Pulp Writer squints."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "How old do you think I am?"
            if (roll writer_menu_two_age_orb orb 80):
                set data.writer.one_age true
                talk orb talk "She's thirty. She'll be thirty-one in a month."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk lovely talk "Abort. Abort. Never ask that question to a milf, Ghost. Milves never realise they're old enough to be a milf, and the revelation is oft enough split their mind asunder. That forbidden knowledge is a Soviet icebreaker crashing between their eyes."
                "\\"You look twenty five.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "I'm twenty five, yes."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_twentyfive_orb orb 20):
                        talk orb talk "She isn't."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    "The Pulp Writer smirks mischievously."
                "\\"Thirty. You'll be thirty-one innnnnnn... [Wiggle your fingers like a magician] A month?\\"" if $data.writer.one_age:
                    talk writer talk "Mhm. Yes. Eerily accurate."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She squints at you."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_twentynine_lovely lovely 40):
                        talk lovely talk "She doesn't like that you were right, but she's rational enough not to be angry at you for being right either."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_twentynine_orb orb 60):
                        talk orb talk "She's also slightly worried you're a police spy. It wouldn't be the first time."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "\\"You look thirty.\\"" if (!= $data.writer.one_age true):
                    talk writer talk "Mhm. Yes. Thirty..."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_thirty_lovely lovely 40):
                        talk lovely talk "She doesn't like that you were right, but she's rational enough not to be angry at you for being right either."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "\\"You look forty.\\"":
                    "There is a moment of silence."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "Hmm. Maybe."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk lovely talk "Yowch."
                    talk nasty talk "Oof."
                "[Shrug] \\"I don't know? A million?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Hmm. Maybe."
                "\\"Milf.\\"":
                    "She smiles."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "I'm perhaps too barren to be a milf, but thank you. That's genuinely a compliment."
                "\\"I'm going to make the objectively correct decision to back out of this discussion and change the subject.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Hmm."
            jump writer_one_menu_two
        "\\"You keep speaking Frankish. Also you sound Frankish. Are you Frankish? I promise I won't make fun of you for being Frankish if you say oui.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Oui."
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Je suis de 'Frankreich'."
                "[Nod] \\"Cool. Je ne pas aus der Frankreich.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Mhm. Clearly."
                "[Point] \\"Baguette! Fromage! Pomme!\\"":
                    "The Pulp Writer points back at you, her finger is millimetres from the tip of your nose."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "Tête de noeud."
                        "\\"Thanks.\\" [Smile and nod your head at the compliment(?)]":
                            talk writer talk "De rien."
                            clear_dialog
                            "They break into a small chuckle."
                            clear_dialog
                            talk lovely talk "They're genuinely amused, but maybe give the <span class='writtenText'>'baguette'</span> stuff a rest, oui?"
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "I was born in Pawris, and I lived there for most of my life. I do not miss it."
            if (roll writer_one_menu_two_frankreich_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "Yes she does."
            else:
                wait 1000
            if (roll writer_one_menu_two_frankreich_orb orb 40):
                talk orb talk "She used to walk along the Marne every day, regardless of the weather. The smell of cigarettes overpowers the smell of sewage in Pawris, and the buildings along the river felt like friends to her, even with the black crown hanging over them. She doesn't walk much these days. She gets out of breath *very* quickly."
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump writer_one_menu_two
        "\\"So. What's <span class='writtenText'>'Sous la couronne noire ou : Ciel d'épines'</span> about?\\"":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "It's a novel discussing the effects of putting out cigarettes on a book. Nothing more."
                "\\"Oh. You're joking. You're not going to tell me what it's really about, are you?\\"":
                    "She sniffs. Her breathing is somewhat okay today, and she'd like to make the most of it."
                "\\"That's cool. Very artistic.\\"":
                    "She sniffs. Her breathing is somewhat okay today, and she'd like to make the most of it."
            jump writer_one_menu_two
        "\\"How would you describe yourself. Like, with words?\\" <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            talk writer talk "You know. That's not something I've ever really thought about."
            if (roll writer_one_menu_two_words_lovely lovely 60):
                talk lovely talk "She's listing words in her head now. Sick. Craven. Bitter. Wasted."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer scratches the back of their hand. The resulting motion looses some ash from her smoke, leaving a little flickering pile atop Sous la couronne noire ou : Ciel d'épines."
            "The tome briefly considers catching fire, but decides not to."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "I'm an afterthought."
                "\\"Nice. Same.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "We all are. It's okay."
                "\\"Sorry to hear that. I'm thinking about you right now though, if that makes you feel better.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "It doesn't, but thank you."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_thanks_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "It does make her feel better, actually."
                        talk nasty talk "This bich not giving anything to us straight good for her good for her."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "What else is there to say? My career can be summed up in a sentence: Dead."
            if (roll writer_one_menu_two_dead_orb orb 20):
                talk orb talk "That was a word, not a sentence."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Other than that? Well, the government thinks I'm a card carrying communist and potential enemy of the state, so I have that going for me."
            choice:
                talk writer talk "I've mellowed with age though, if I push them anymore they might deport me back to Pawris, pour mes péchés, which I, cowardly, would rather avoid for now, I'm not going back to that piss soaked graveyard..."
                "\\"Oh no!\\"":
                    talk writer talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Oh no!'</span> is right, yes. It's not fun to find your post pre opened by the security services."
                    talk writer talk "Not that I blame them, I suppose I *am* somewhat of a card carrying communist and potential enemy of the state."
                "\\"*Are* you a card carrying communist and potential enemy of the state?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Well, I suppose so yes."
                "\\"I don't personally thing there's anything wrong with being piss soaked. I'm just putting that out there.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Hmm. Okay. Noted."
            clear_dialog
            "She studies the lit end of her cigarette. It bores her. You catch her glancing at you, then away."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "I was fired from my previous job after trying to form a writers union, and the post office once intercepted me writing to the Premier of the Soviet Republic informing him that <span class='writtenText'>'the west yearns for freedom'</span> and requesting he post me a <span class='writtenText'>'crate of his finest 120mm ordnance'</span>."
            talk writer talk "Also I posted money to the Corvid Commune, though I managed to talk my way out of a treason charge by pretending it was the wrong address."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Also I'm a member of a Frankish communist parties which yes, came with a card."
                "\\"Can I see your card?\\"":
                    talk writer talk "I suppose so."
                    clear_dialog
                    play sound clothing
                    run transition writer_sofa_card
                    "The Pulp Writer searches through her coat pocket, and pulls out a grimy, crumpled card adorned with incredibly anal grammatical corrections."
                    clear_dialog
                    run transition writer_card
                    choice:
                        "You take the card from her. In this moment *you* are the card carrying communist."
                        "\\"I feel as though the weight of all the workers of the world stands with me.\\"":
                            talk writer talk "Mhm. Maybe."
                        "\\"<span class='writtenText'>'CSCPCSEIFECAN'</span>?\\"":
                            talk lovely talk "Bless you."
                            clear_dialog
                            talk writer talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Le CHAMP SYNDICALISTE COMBINÉ et le PARTI COMMUNISTE des SIDÉRURGISTES et des ÉTUDIANT·ES INTELLECTUEL·LES de FRANKREICH, d'EUROPE CENTRALE et d'AFRIKA DU NORD'</span>. It's the name of the party."
                            if (roll writer_one_menu_two_party_orb orb 40):
                                talk orb talk "It has twenty seven members. Twenty six if you choose to acknowledge that our friends membership expired two years ago."
                            else:
                                wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    play sound clothing
                    run transition writer_sofa
                "\\"Did the Premier ever write back?\\"":
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "No. The intelligence agency burnt the letter before he could read it."
                        "\\"That's a shame. You could have become pen pals.\\"":
                            talk writer talk "Hmm. Maybe."
                            clear_dialog
                            "She thinks."
                            clear_dialog
                            talk writer talk "No. Probably not. His blood is tainted with reaction. The Muskovite revolution has been betrayed by his recent land reforms."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Now."
            clear_dialog
            "Her eyes gleam like razor blades. They cut into your retinas."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "How would *you* describe yourself, Ghost?"
                "[Shrug] \\"I'm cool. I'm a cool lady.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Hmm. Groovy."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_groovy_orb orb 20):
                        talk orb talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Goovy'</span>... that word will be pretty popular in about thirty years. Perhaps our friend here will have more of a legacy than she knows? Maybe don't tell her that though, she'd be disappointed."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "[Shake your head] \\"I'm always a bit stupid and I have amnesia.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Don't be so hard on yourself. It's the 20s, we all *wish* we had amenesia. You're a blessed woman, Ghost."
                "\\"I don't eat enough so I always feel slightly ill and I never wash, which is pretty sexy of me, I think.\\"" if (!= $data.ghost.hadBath true):
                    talk writer talk "It is quite sexy, yes."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk nasty talk "I told you. Women love smelly garbage women."
                    talk lovely talk "She was joking, Nasty Girl."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk writer talk "I'm getting a little grimy myself."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_grime_orb orb 20):
                        talk orb talk "She washed this morning. She's actually very hygienic, weirdly so. She meant that comment in more of a spiritual sense."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "\\"I'm fake trans, the interrogation lamp stringing a noose told me so. It's wrong though, and I'm going to prove it by finding and snorting some oestrogen whether it likes it or not.\\"" if $data.global.diagnosis_fake:
                    talk writer talk "Hmm. Same. Eh, c'est la vie, mhm?"
                "\\"I'm an autogynephile, the interrogation lamp stringing a noose told me so.\\" [Lean in and whisper] \\"That means I like feet.\\" [Wink]" if $data.global.diagnosis_agp:
                    talk writer talk "Nothing wrong with liking feet, not that I do."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk nasty talk "Hahaha, she *so* does."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_feet_orb orb 20):
                        talk orb talk "She doesn't. If she ever saw a bare foot she would actually die."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "\\"I'm an autogynephile, the interrogation lamp stringing a noose told me so.\\" [Lean in and whisper] \\"That means the healthcare system thinks I like feet, but I actually really don't.\\" [Wink] (Lie)" if $data.global.diagnosis_agp:
                    "The Pulp Writer stifles a smirk."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "She knows you're lying. She *knows* you're a foot pervert."
                        "But I'm *not* a foot pervert! Why do people keep calling me a foot pervert!":
                            talk nasty talk "Probably because you're a foot pervert."
                            talk lovely talk "Specifically a foot pervert who keeps saying things like 'Ça alors! Me!? A foot pervert!? Never!' and then starts sweating and tugging on her collar."
                            talk orb talk "It would honestly be less embarrassing if you just owned up to it, Ghost. Alternatively you could consider just *not* bringing up feet unprompted to begin with."
                        "She's got me dead to rights. [Shake your head and erotically wiggle your toes in shame]":
                            talk nasty talk "Foot pervert. If I had a physical form I'd shake your dainty little hand and welcome you to the club with me and Lovely Lady."
                            talk lovely talk "H-hey!"
                "\\"I'm a Type VI Transexual, the interrogation lamp stringing a noose told me so.\\" [Make a wanky face that makes you look like a Type VI Dickhead]" if $data.global.diagnosis_iv:
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "Hmm. Une transexuelle... that's nice. I'm straddling the line between fake trans and autogynephile myself. Good for you though. Do you get a certificate?"
                        "No, but the pride lives in my heart none the less.":
                            talk writer talk "Mhm."
                "\\"I'm an investor. I'm making it big on the stork market.\\"" if $data.ghost.investor:
                    talk writer talk "Mmm. Yes I bet."
                    if (!= $data.ghost.cleanClothes true):
                        clear_dialog
                        "She looks at your dirty clothes and general 'dirt poor' aura."
                "\\"I'm a no good sack of shit. The scary mechanic in town told me. It made me sad but in retrospect it was kind of hot how she picked me up and threatened to kill me.\\"" if $data.ghost.sackOfShit:
                    choice:
                        "The Pump Writer blinks at you. She's unsure how to respond to this."
                        "\\"I mean I'm nice, haha. I'm normal :)\\"":
                            talk writer talk "So I see, yes."
                "\\"I simply wouldn't.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Then you're a wiser woman than me."
                    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_wise_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "She's actually disappointed. She was genuinely quite curious. It's too late to turn back now though, this one is on borrowed time. She refuses to linger."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Anyhow."
            jump writer_one_leave

writer_one_leave:
    clear_dialog
    "They stub their cigarette out on Ciel d'epintes."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "I need to get this to the editor, along with my own article. So I bid you a fond au revoir."
        "\\"What's your article about?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Ghosts. 'Actual' ones. Off you go now."
            talk lovely talk "Rude."
        "\\"I wish you a very 'Au revoir' too.\\"":
            talk lovely talk "You don't speak Frankish. Don't try."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Oh. I almost did forget."
    talk writer talk "We have another piece for you to do. A short fiction piece of your choosing, as long as it quote <span class='writtenText'>'vibes with the Weird Tails values and ethos and isn't paced too flabbily'</span>, as if that exists."
    clear_dialog
    "She rolls her eyes."
    if (roll writer_one_menu_two_fiction_lovely lovely 40):
        talk lovely talk "She *really* hates the editor, and just about anything he says. <span class='writtenText'>'What the fuck does 'flabby' mean, dickhead?'.</span>"
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "We'll need an author biography from you too, actually. Could you write up one of those? Usually we publish one alongside your first article, but our dickhead boss didn't want to detract from the troops. Also he sold the spot it would have gone in as ad space for a line of lead flavour condoms."
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Just a paragraph or two about you. Nothing too self-masturbatory, but enough to give you some credibility as a writer. Our shit eating boss is really pushing for Tails to <span class='writtenText'>'remedy its public perception'</span> after the <span class='writtenText'>'heresy scandal'</span>."
        "\\"The what scandal?\\"":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "It doesn't matter. Just get that biography and article written by the end of tomorrow, yes? It's short notice, I apologise, but that's our dickhead boss for you, ouais?"                   
                "[Nod] \\"I'll have it done by the end of tomorrow, I promise.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Good."
                "[Nod] \\"I'll make you proud, fellow writer.\\" [Salute them]":
                    "She rolls her eyes under her breath. Somehow."
    start_objective writer fiction
    clear_dialog
    play sound dooropen
    "The Pulp Writer stands up and leads you to the door. You expect her to slam it behind you, but she doesn't. She takes a moment to look at you. She has an expression, though it isn't one you can read."
    if (roll writer_one_leave_expression_lovely lovely 40):
        talk lovely talk "She's sad to see you go. She was enjoying your company. Your company *and* your pretty smile."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    run transition generic_winter
    choice:
        talk writer talk "See you, Ghost."
        "<span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            play sound doorclose
            jump goToGameMap

writer_one_badEnd:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Tell me, did you come all the way here to fuck me in the ass like this because you hate me, or do you just get off on making yourself look like a jackass?"
        "\\"Um. Yes?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Ugh."
        "\\"Excuse me?\\"":
            talk writer talk "I can't send this to the boss. He won't publish it, and for once I agree with him. You're meant to be a professional, for fucks sake, you think we hired you to write shit that'll make people think Weird Tails is somehow even more of a tabloid than it already is?"
    clear_dialog
    if $data.article.orbFuckedUp:
        talk nasty talk "Orb fucked up! Dumb cunts probably fucked our chances of getting some depressed milf pussy!"
        talk orb talk "Look, I did tell you it was a bad idea to rely soley on my memory. You could have just gone and done your job properly, you know?"
    else:
        talk orb talk "Loathe as I am to sound like a smug asshole, I told you we should have done this properly."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "Why did you even bother to show up? Just to mock me? I'm going to have to write some fucking filler now. Some sheepshit about there being too many pigeons in the park or something. Fucking hel. I cannot believe you had to nerve to accept a drink off of me only to hand me this shit!? Putain de dieu, je dois tout faire pour this fucking rag!"
    if (roll writer_one_badEnd_actually_orb orb 60):
        talk orb talk "Actually, she's already written an article. She never had any faith in you, or indeed anyone else."
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            "The Pulp Writer glares at you. Your silence frustrates her."
            "\\"A reliable source informs me that you already wrote an article, so actually everything is fine, actually. [Lean in and wink] How's that for being a journalist?\\"":
                "The Pulp Writer takes a small amount of damage. Her eyes crack open like eggs, unnaturally wide, for just the briefest moment."
                clear_dialog
                talk writer talk "How did you..."
                clear_dialog
                "She scowls."
                clear_dialog
                talk writer talk "That's not the point! The point is you're... you're..."
                choice:
                    talk writer talk "Just fuck off!"
                    "[Fuck off]":
                        clear_dialog
                        play sound doorclose
                        run transition generic_winter
    else:
        wait 1000
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            "The Pulp Writer glares at you. Your silence frustrates her."
            "\\"I'm really sorry. Can I help you?\\"":
                choice:
                    talk writer talk "Help me? This is your fucking mess to begin with! Just get out. Please. I need to write something before we end up with a blank page for the boss to hold over my head."
                    "[Get out]":
                        clear_dialog
                        play sound doorclose
                        run transition generic_winter
    clear_dialog
    complete_quest writer writerLate
    choice:
        talk orb talk "We probably should have done our job properly huh."
        "Hmm. Maybe next time. <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            complete_objective writer article
            jump goToGameMap